With about 7 year’s management experience of a small grocery store, Ynes Altagracia is an assiduous entrepreneur that works harder and harder in order to improve her family’s situation.  She’s 50 year old and she has 3 sons who live with their own families.  Currently, Ynes lives with her grandsons.  Her husband is a carpenter.
Ynes Altagracia is asking for a loan to buy more products to add to her store.  She says that with the amount requested, she’ll be able to purchase 4 crates of beer (a crate contains 24 bottles).  In Villa Estrella, the community wherein she operates her grocery store, people love to consume beer, and she practically has to be purchasing the beverages about two times a month.  The entrepreneur, also leader of the group, hopes that her business will be more successful and that she’ll be able to repay the loan quickly.  That way, she’ll be entitled to receive a larger loan in the future.
The other members of Ynes Altagracia’s group are:
Andrea Abelina L. M., who sells clothing;
Evelyn M., who sells women’s clothing;
Paula M., who sells footwear;
Siveline A., who operates a fruit and vegetable stand;
In the picture, from left to right: Ynes Altagracia, Andrea, Evelyn, Paula and Siveline.
